item.title: Business warns of $400b virus economic hit
item.description: Australian businesses have warned the national economy could take a $400 billion hit if coronavirus restrictions are kept in place for six months.

item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
One million Aussies download COVIDSafe app
item.description: More than one million Australians have downloaded the coronavirus tracing app within hours of its release.

item.title: Warriors already at a disadvantage: Green
item.description: Halfback Blake Green believes the Warriors are at a disadvantage compared to every other NRL club skill and fitness-wise because of New Zealand's stricter lockdown regulations.

item.title: New Zealand coronavirus death toll now 19
item.description: As New Zealand prepares to lessen its severe lockdown, health authorities have reported another death linked to COVID-19.

item.title: Aristocrat Leisure cuts jobs, pay, payout
item.description: Gaming giant Aristocrat Leisure will cut staff and impose pay cuts on employees and management and won't declare a dividend as it copes with the fallout from COVID-19 lockdowns.

item.title: NAB slashes H1 payout, to raise $3.5bn
item.description: National Australia Bank has slashed its interim dividend to 30 cents and launched a $3.5 billion capital raising in a bid to buttress itself against a virus-driven economic downturn that helped to more than halve its first-half cash earnings.

item.title: Six feared missing found in WA’s north
item.description: A hunting group of three men, two women and a child, who were feared missing in Western Australia's Kimberley region, have been found safe and well.

item.title: Major drop in Qld flu cases amid pandemic
item.description: Flu cases have taken an enormous dive in Queensland just months after one of the state's worst seasons on record claimed the lives of 264 people.

item.title: Asia shares ahead, eyes on Bank of Japan
item.description: Asian shares inched higher on Monday ahead of a busy week for earnings and central bank meetings, with much chatter the Bank of Japan (BOJ) will announce more stimulus steps.
